frames.description: Opening VS Code by clicking on the dock icon
VS Code launches with welcome screen, showing recent projects
Clicking on 'Open Folder' button to open project directory
File dialog opens, navigating to ~/projects/web-app directory
Selecting project folder and clicking 'Open' to load project
Project loads with file explorer showing on left, main.js file visible
Double-clicking on main.js file in explorer to open it
main.js file opens in editor, showing 150 lines of JavaScript code
Scrolling down to line 75 where there's a function definition
Clicking at the end of line 78 to position cursor for editing
Typing new code: 'console.log("Debug: user data", userData);'
Pressing Cmd+S to save the file, file indicator shows saved
Opening integrated terminal by pressing Ctrl+` (backtick)
Terminal panel opens at bottom, showing command prompt
Typing 'npm run dev' command to start development server
Pressing Enter to execute the command, server starting up
Development server starts, showing 'Server running on localhost:3000'
Switching to Chrome browser to test the application
Typing 'localhost:3000' in address bar to access local server
Web application loads in browser, displaying the homepage
Clicking on 'Login' button to test authentication flow
Login form appears, entering test credentials
Submitting login form, page redirects to dashboard
Opening Chrome DevTools by pressing F12 to check console
Console tab shows the debug message we added: 'Debug: user data'
Switching back to VS Code to continue development
Opening styles.css file from file explorer to update styling
Adding new CSS rule for button hover effects
Saving CSS changes with Cmd+S, preparing to test updates
